<p>You have two choices to explore the volcano and view it&rsquo;s majestic turquoise crater lake. One option is to use the local tourism cooperative who will arrange transportation to and from the volcano entering from the town of Cosig&uuml;ina.</p>

<p>The second option involves taking the local bus and spending the night at Brisas de Gulfo, a local family run hotel in Potosi. Rafael, the hotel owner, can arrange for you to hike with local guides.</p>

